title: $:/plugins/rimir/worga/changelog
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! Changelog

|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.0.7 |2026-05-31 |''Pick attendees toggle action rewritten as a single $action-sendmessage with inline-filter `$message` (views/pick-attendees.tid).'' 0.0.5/0.0.6 used two mutually-exclusive `<$list>` widgets to dispatch pin vs unpin. The list-iteration approach didn't fire reliably from `ca-view-row-actions` (Enter on a row didn't toggle even after the cp 0.0.96 ca-view-after-fire fix). Switched to a single `<$action-sendmessage $message={{{ [enlist<sticky-context-list>match<currentTiddler>then[rimir-cascade-palette-unpin-context]else[rimir-cascade-palette-pin-context]] }}} title=<<currentTiddler>>/>` — one widget, one filter evaluated at fire time picking the right message name. Same `title` parameter works for both messages so the disambiguation is purely in `$message`. Pattern matches the simple `<$action-navigate $to=<<currentTiddler>>/>` shape that cp's built-in tree views (by-namespace, by-parent, by-date) use for `ca-view-row-actions` — single action widget, no nested conditional flow. ''Touches:'' `views/pick-attendees.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler only — restart required. |
|0.0.6 |2026-05-31 |''Exclude system tiddlers from `attendees-roots-filter` (config/attendees-roots-filter.tid).'' 0.0.5's fix changed the broken `get[kind.type]match[person]` chain to `field:kind.type[person]`, but the new filter also matches the kind plugin's TYPE DEFINITION tiddler at `$:/config/rimir/kind/types/person`: kind self-describes — its type tiddlers carry the very `kind.type` value they define. So the filter returned BOTH the type def AND every actual person instance, surfacing "person" alongside "Liliya Miertzschke" in the picker. Added `!is[system]` to both filter clauses: `[all[tiddlers]field:kind.type[person]!is[system]] [all[tiddlers]tag[Person]!is[system]]`. Type defs live under `$:/config/...` (system), real person instances don't, so the predicate cleanly separates them. ''Touches:'' `config/attendees-roots-filter.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler only — restart required. Companion to cascade-palette 0.0.96 which finally makes `ca-view-after-fire: stay` (the view-level keep-open this view was relying on) work. Without 0.0.96 the toggle on Enter fires but the palette closes anyway. |
|0.0.5 |2026-05-31 |''Pick attendees becomes a real multiselect — checkbox row icons, pinned-first sort, Enter toggles in or out.'' Three changes, one bug fix. ''(1) Fixed broken roots filter (config/attendees-roots-filter.tid).'' Was `[all[tiddlers]has[kind.type]get[kind.type]match[person]] [all[tiddlers]tag[Person]]` — the first clause's `get[kind.type]` REPLACES titles with the field value "person", so the filter returned the literal string `"person"` as a row instead of actual person tiddlers. Fixed with `field:kind.type[person]` which keeps titles intact AND filters by value: `[all[tiddlers]field:kind.type[person]] [all[tiddlers]tag[Person]]`. Same broken pattern was in worga's `take-call.tid` `ca-applies` filter but THAT one is fine because ca-applies just checks "non-empty result = applies" — the result content doesn't matter there. ''(2) Pin-state row icon (views/pick-attendees.tid `ca-view-row-icon`).'' `[enlist<sticky-context-list>match<currentTiddler>then[☑]else[☐]]` — pinned rows show ☑, unpinned show ☐. The `then`/`else` filter operators are TW's "replace input if non-empty / replace input if empty" pair — chains directly off `match<currentTiddler>` returning [currentTiddler] when in the list, [] when not. ''(3) Pinned-first sort (`ca-view-sort: custom` + `ca-view-sort-key`).'' Sort key per row: `[enlist<sticky-context-list>match<currentTiddler>then[0]else[1]addsuffix<currentTiddler>]` → produces "0<title>" for pinned, "1<title>" for unpinned. localeCompare puts "0" before "1", so pinned float to the top; alphabetic order is the natural tiebreaker within each group. ''(4) Enter toggles instead of pin-only (`ca-view-row-actions`).'' Two mutually-exclusive `<$list>` blocks, each iterates exactly once or not at all: list 1 with filter `[<currentTiddler>] -[enlist<sticky-context-list>]` fires `pin-context` only when current row is NOT pinned; list 2 with filter `[enlist<sticky-context-list>] +[match<currentTiddler>]` fires `unpin-context` only when current row IS pinned. Single line per field per TW's `.tid` parser. The cp engine evaluates `ca-view-row-actions` as a filter first and falls back to the raw string when filter eval produces nothing — the `<$list>` wikitext goes through the fallback path and is dispatched as an action chain at fire time. ''Touches:'' `config/attendees-roots-filter.tid`, `views/pick-attendees.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddlers only — restart required for the shadow updates to land. |
|0.0.4 |2026-05-31 |''`take-call` now also jumps to the "Topics for context" view after pinning (actions/take-call.tid).'' Symmetric with `start-meeting` (which jumps to "Pick attendees") — the action becomes a single-keystroke "I'm in a call with this person, show me the topics" macro instead of just pinning and leaving the user to switch views manually. Action chain is now three messages: `clear-context` → `pin-context` → `set-view: $:/plugins/rimir/worga/views/topics-for-context`. Hint updated. ''Touches:'' `actions/take-call.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler changed — restart required. |
|0.0.3 |2026-05-31 |''`take-call` keeps the palette open after firing (actions/take-call.tid).'' Added `ca-after-fire: keep` to mirror the same change on cp-core's `sticky-context-pin` / `-unpin` shadows (cascade-palette 0.0.95). Single-keystroke entry into a call now leaves the palette focused on the action menu so the user can follow up immediately (switch to "Topics for context", take notes, pin another attendee, etc.) without re-opening cp. ''Touches:'' `actions/take-call.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. Shadow tiddler changed — restart required. |
|0.0.2 |2026-05-30 |''Bug fixes: single-line `ca-actions` field values + correct `:intersection` per-topic predicate.'' Two corrections to 0.0.1. ''(1) Multi-line `ca-actions` / `ca-leader-actions` (take-call.tid + start-meeting.tid).'' TW `.tid` field syntax allows ONE line per field — the next non-`name: value` line is treated as body content. 0.0.1's `take-call.tid` had two `<$action-sendmessage>` widgets separated by a literal newline inside `ca-actions`; only `clear-context` actually fired. Same defect in `start-meeting.tid` `ca-leader-actions` — `clear-context` fired but `set-view` did not, so `m` cleared the context without switching to the pick-attendees view. Both files now concatenate the two action widgets onto one line. ''(2) Per-topic intersection in `topics-for-context.tid` (NEW `macros.tid`).'' 0.0.1's view filter used `:filter[<currentTiddler>get[stakeholders]enlist-input[] +[enlist<sticky-context-list>]]` — incorrect because `+[enlist<X>]` REPLACES the accumulator with the enlist'd titles (the `+` prefix sets source = prior, but `enlist<X>` is a source-emitter and ignores its source), silently matching every topic. Fixed by extracting a `\function worga.any-pinned-stakeholder(topic)` into the new `macros.tid` (tagged `$:/tags/Macro`, picked up by cp's startup `\import`) that uses the proper `:intersection[enlist<sticky-context-list>]` per-topic. View tiddler now calls `:filter[function[worga.any-pinned-stakeholder],<currentTiddler>]` (explicit-arg form per the `tw-gotchas-widget-context#filter functions and <currentTiddler> binding` defensive recommendation). Verified at the CLI level that nested-bracket inline `:intersection` inside `:filter[predicate]` silently produces wrong results — extracting to a named function bypasses the parser issue AND makes the helper reusable. ''Touches:'' `actions/take-call.tid`, `leaders/start-meeting.tid`, new `macros.tid`, `views/topics-for-context.tid`, `readme.tid`, `doc/overview.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. JS modules unchanged; tiddler restart required for the new shadow values to land. |
|0.0.1 |2026-05-30 |Initial scaffold. TW `.tid` field syntax requires each field's value on a single line (the next non-blank line that isn't `key: value` is treated as body content). 0.0.1's `actions/take-call.tid` had two `<$action-sendmessage>` widgets separated by a literal newline inside `ca-actions`; only the first (`clear-context`) actually fired. Same defect in `leaders/start-meeting.tid` `ca-leader-actions` — `clear-context` fired but `set-view` did not, so `m` cleared the context without switching to the pick-attendees view. Both files now concatenate the two action widgets onto one line. ''Touches:'' `actions/take-call.tid`, `leaders/start-meeting.tid`, `plugin.info`, `changelog.tid`. No JS modules; tiddler restart required for the new shadow values to land. |
|0.0.1 |2026-05-30 |Initial scaffold. Three shipped tiddlers demonstrating how to layer workday workflows on top of `rimir/cascade-palette`'s sticky-context mechanism: ''`actions/take-call.tid`'' (universal "Take call from <person>" verb — clears context then pins the row), ''`leaders/start-meeting.tid`'' (`m` leader; drills into the pick-attendees view), ''`views/pick-attendees.tid`'' (`ca-view-after-fire: stay` so successive Enters append picks to context), ''`views/topics-for-context.tid`'' (worked example of a context-aware view with `ca-view-context-aware: yes`). Three config tiddlers (`topics-stakeholder-field` / `topics-roots-filter` / `attendees-roots-filter`) let users adapt the filters to their data model without forking. Soft-deps `cascade-palette` ≥ 0.0.92 and (optionally) `kind`. |
